news.title: Many properties sold to multiple owners, realtors: Chandigarh administration report
news.para: The report was submitted by UT chief architect. In one instance, a property in Sector 22 had four sale deeds, another had five. A developer bought a property and sold it to other people. The report also highlights floor-wise sale in these properties in different parts of the city.

news.title: Livspace plans to invest $50 million to expand its business
news.para: Livspace which claims to hold a 65% market share in the organised home interiors sector, also plans to set up 150 Design Experience Centre (ECs) over the next 18 months.

news.title: Nagpur civic body regularized unauthorized layout, plots for 20 months without authority
news.para: ​To avoid inconvenience to people, the state government has reportedly assured to come up with a plan where the decisions taken by the civic body will be regularized.

news.title: Asian Granito targets exports of Rs 400 crore in FY22
news.para: The company said anti-China sentiments, lower duties on export to the United States, robust export orders from Europe, the Middle East, the United Kingdom and the United States are driving Indian exports.

news.title: Action against three officials for irregularities under PMAY in Barmer
news.para: Zila parishad CEO Mohandan Ratnu said for being careless in implementation and irregularities in yojana and departmental inquiry being under consideration

news.title: Rajasthan: New amendment likely to reduce tenant-owner row
news.para: UDH minister Shanti Dhariwal said, “The move would help police in identifying the tenants in case of any dispute. It would be easier for either of the parties, tenant or owner, to exercise legal rights judiciously.”

news.title: Gurugram: 11 shops razed and 13 buildings sealed in DLF-3
news.para: Also, 11 shops constructed on residential plots were demolished by the enforcement team, he added. The demolition drive was carried out in S and U blocks of DLF-3 with the help of 50 labourers and two earthmovers.

news.title: NBCC sells unused FAR of Amrapali project at Rs 43 crore
news.para: NBCC is expected to raise Rs 1,500 crore from the sale of unused FAR in the housing projects of embattled real estate developer Amrapali Group. The developer, which is part of Express Projects (P) Ltd, is expected to construct six residential towers.

news.title: Over 9,200 properties sealed from 2018 to Aug 31: DDA
news.para: ​The Delhi Development Authority, whose vice chairman heads the STF, said actions taken till August 31 include those taken by the Monitoring Committee as well.

news.title: PNB cuts rate on home loan above Rs 50 lakh by 50 basis points
news.para: "In a series of offers launched by Punjab National Bank during the festival season, PNB has cut the interest rate on home loans above Rs 50 lakh by 50 basis points (0.50 per cent).

news.title: IIFL Home Finance inks co-lending pact with Punjab National Bank
news.para: "IIFL HFL today announced and signed an agreement with PNB, India's 2nd largest public sector bank, for co-lending. The loan sourcing and servicing will be managed by IIFL Home Finance and 80 per cent of the loan will be provided by PNB," it said.

news.title: HC seeks DLF Home Developers, authorities' reply over alleged commercial use of green space
news.para: ​​A bench of Chief Justices D N Patel and Justice Jyoti Singh issued notice on the plea by two organisations and also sought response from DLF Home Developers, North Delhi Municipal Corporation, Delhi Jal Board and others.

news.title: Promoters to hand over societies to AOAs by September 30: Noida Authority
news.para: ​Noida Authority CEO Ritu Maheshwari issued the direction after a meeting here on the builder-buyers issues with AOAs and real estate developers, including Supertech Group, Mahagun Group, Prateek Group, ATS, RG Residency, Sunshine Infrawell and Perfect Propbuild.

news.title: Berlin to buy 15,000 flats for $2.90 billion from Vonovia & Deutsche Wohnen
news.para: The acquisition comes nine days before elections in the German capital, where housing shortages and rapidly rising prices have become a hot issue. An advisory referendum on expropriating the two housing companies is due to be held in parallel with the city election.

news.title: China's nightmare Evergrande scenario is an uncontrolled crash
news.para: Evergrande’s main banks were told by China’s housing ministry this week that the developer won’t be able to make interest payments due Sept. 20, according to people familiar with the matter.
